results.name: Number of numbers m such that the sum of the anti-divisors of m is n+1.
comment: See A066272 for definition of anti-divisor.
link: Jon Perry, The Anti-divisor: Even More Anti-Divisors [Cached copy]
example: 8 has anti-divisors 1, 3 and 5, whose sum is 9 and 9 has anti-divisors 1, 2 and 6, whose sum is 9 and there are no others. Therefore a(8)=2.
results.author: _Jon Perry_, Dec 28 2001
